27/10/2010
BERLIN, Germany -- Foreign Minister Guido Westerwelle is urging Turkish Cypriot leader Dervis Eroglu to demonstrate tolerance and flexibility in order to successfully complete ongoing talks to reunify Cyprus.
"Turkish as well as Greek Cypriots should lead the negotiations over the reunification of their island seriously and with a real will to unify," Westerwelle said after meeting with Eroglu in Berlin on Tuesday (October 26th).
Westerwelle added that Berlin "understands" the hopes and concerns of Turkish Cypriots and expressed his country's readiness to help reach a solution.
(DPA, Anadolu news agency, World Bulletin - 26/10/10)
